<%- include('../../Solutions-Card/solutionsCard.ejs') %>

<div class="privacy-policy-container">
  <div class="main-heading">
    <h1>PRIVACY POLICY</h1>
  </div>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Comprehensive Information Collection</h2>
  <p>
    Our data collection methodology is robust, multi-layered, and continuously
    evolving. We may collect, store, and process the following categories of
    information, including but not limited to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Personally Identifiable Information (PII): This includes your full legal
      name, username, contact number, email address, physical address,
      geolocation data, biometric identifiers, government-issued identification
      numbers (where applicable), and any information that may directly or
      indirectly identify you.
    </li>
    <li>
      Device and Usage Information: Browser type, device model, OS version, IP
      address, MAC address, unique device identifiers, session timestamps,
      referring pages, and engagement patterns across our Platform.
    </li>
    <li>
      Behavioral and Preference Data: Click paths, scrolling behavior,
      time-on-page, cursor movements, interactions with media elements, survey
      responses, language preferences, and communication history.
    </li>
    <li>
      Third-Party Data: Information acquired from third-party integrations,
      advertising networks, analytics platforms, social media APIs, or affiliate
      partners. This may be combined with your existing profile for deeper
      profiling.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Legal Basis and Purpose of Processing</h2>
  <p>
    All data processing is executed under lawful bases, including but not
    limited to legitimate interest, performance of a contract, user consent, and
    compliance with legal obligations. The purposes for which your information
    is used include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Enhancing operational efficiency, product reliability, and user
      satisfaction.
    </li>
    <li>
      Personalizing content, interface behavior, and advertising based on
      predictive analytics.
    </li>
    <li>
      Conducting audits, performance reviews, debugging, penetration testing,
      and data integrity checks.
    </li>
    <li>
      Initiating, processing, and resolving financial transactions or
      account-related procedures.
    </li>
    <li>
      Complying with legal mandates, subpoenas, government audits, and
      regulatory oversight.
    </li>
    <li>
      Facilitating internal reporting, cross-department collaboration, and
      strategic forecasting.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Security Measures and Limitations</h2>
  <p>
    We implement an exhaustive array of technical, administrative, and physical
    safeguards to preserve the integrity and confidentiality of your data. These
    include multi-factor authentication protocols, zero-trust architecture,
    end-to-end encryption, SSL/TLS certificates, firewalls, AI-powered anomaly
    detection systems, and periodic penetration testing conducted by certified
    professionals. Nevertheless, no system can guarantee absolute
    impenetrability. You acknowledge that by using our services, you accept the
    inherent risks of data transmission over untrusted networks.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Use of Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
  <p>
    Our Platform utilizes cookies, web beacons, local storage, fingerprinting,
    heatmaps, and third-party tracking pixels to gather telemetry data. These
    elements are essential for delivering optimal functionality, maintaining
    session continuity, monitoring analytics, executing marketing campaigns, and
    diagnosing service issues. By continuing to use our Platform, you consent to
    the deployment of these technologies. You may alter cookie preferences via
    your browser; however, doing so may impact user experience, disable
    features, or prevent access to certain sections of the Platform.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Data Sharing and Third-Party Disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal information for direct profit. However, data
    may be shared with third parties under the following conditions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Service Providers: Entities that provide hosting, security, analytics,
      email delivery, customer support, or development assistance.
    </li>
    <li>
      Legal Authorities: Courts, law enforcement, and regulatory bodies when
      legally compelled to do so.
    </li>
    <li>
      Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, restructuring,
      or asset sale, your information may be transferred as part of our business
      continuity.
    </li>
    <li>
      Advertising & Analytics Partners: To provide targeted marketing,
      remarketing, and performance analysis.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These parties are contractually bound to uphold confidentiality and data
    protection standards that meet or exceed our own.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Data Retention and Deletion Policy</h2>
  <p>
    Your information is stored for the duration necessary to fulfill the
    purposes for which it was collected, to satisfy legal, contractual, and
    operational requirements, and to support legitimate business interests. Data
    may be retained indefinitely in anonymized or pseudonymized form for
    research, trend analysis, and archival purposes. Deletion requests are
    reviewed on a case-by-case basis and may be denied if they conflict with
    legal obligations or operational needs.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">International Data Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    If you are accessing our Platform from a jurisdiction outside of our primary
    operational territory, you understand and consent that your data may be
    transferred to, processed in, and stored in countries with different data
    protection laws, which may not offer the same level of protection as your
    home jurisdiction. We take steps to ensure your data is treated securely and
    in accordance with this Policy regardless of where it is processed.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">User Rights and Control</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to request access to
    your personal data, rectify inaccuracies, object to processing, restrict
    processing, withdraw consent, and request data portability. To exercise any
    of these rights, contact us using the information below. We may require
    proof of identity before acting on such requests. We reserve the right to
    deny requests that are unreasonable, repetitive, technically infeasible, or
    would require disproportionate effort.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Minors and Data Collection</h2>
  <p>
    Our services are not directed toward individuals under the age of 13 (or the
    applicable age of digital consent in your region). We do not knowingly
    collect or solicit personal information from minors. If we become aware of
    any such collection, we will take immediate action to delete the data.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Modifications to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Policy is subject to change without prior notification. Updates will be
    posted to this page with an updated “Last Revised” date. You are responsible
    for reviewing this Policy periodically. Continued use of the Platform
    following any changes constitutes binding acceptance of those changes.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">
    Enforcement, Violations, and Dispute Resolution
  </h2>
  <p>
    Any breach of this Policy may result in restricted access, termination of
    services, or legal action. Disputes arising from this Policy shall be
    governed by the laws of the governing jurisdiction and resolved through
    binding arbitration, unless otherwise mandated by law.
  </p>

  <h2 class="secondary-heading">Contact Information</h2>
  <p>
    For questions, concerns, or data requests related to this Policy, please
    contact our Data Protection Officer (DPO) at:
    <br />
    <strong>Email:</strong> info@digitalbenders.ca<br />
    <strong>Mail:</strong> Digital Benders, Legal Department, Karachi,
    Pakistan<br />
    <strong>Phone:</strong> XXXX-XXXX-XXX
  </p>
</div>
